@emmanuel most of this looks great. The only question I have is why `#set_attributes` accepts the `include_private` argument, yet doesn't use it for anything.

I thought we were going to make it so that `#attributes=` called `#set_attributes` with a subset of the attributes that are non-private, and that calling `#set_attributes` directly it would just do what it was told?

Also, I wouldn't be againast naming `#set_attributes` as `#set`, although that's probably up for discussion on whether or not it makes the private interface "too pretty", thus making it more likely for it to be (ab)used without bringing attention to the fact that it is kind of dangerous.

